  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When batch verifying signatures we can set the multiplier of the first signature to 1. Currently it looks to be set to a random number, as the other multipliers are. \r\n\r\nThis _might_ save us a scalar multiplication in the batch verifier. However, since Blst appears to do constant time multiplication, it might make no difference ðŸ™‚ Anyway, possibly worth investigating.\r\n\r\nThis optimisation was suggested by Vitalik in his [original article](https://ethresear.ch/t/fast-verification-of-multiple-bls-signatures/5407) on batch verification.",
